This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as machine translation. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new learning approach for sequence-to-sequence models. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of recurrent neural networks for language modeling. The paper also mentions parameter sharing, which is a common technique in neural network optimization, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions experiments on image captioning, which could place it under cs.CV (Computer Vision).
